verses.text:
Bless the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, O my soul. O 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* my God , thou art very great ; thou art clothed with honour and majesty. \q1
Who coverest \add thyself\add* with light as \add with\add* a garment : who stretchest out the heavens like a curtain : \q1
Who layeth the beams of his chambers in the waters : who maketh the clouds his chariot : who walketh upon the wings of the wind : \q1
Who maketh his angels spirits ; his ministers a flaming fire : \q1
\add Who\add* laid the foundations of the earth , \add that\add* it should not be removed for ever.\f + \fr 104.5 \ft Who…: Heb. He hath founded the earth upon her bases\f* \q1
Thou coveredst it with the deep as \add with\add* a garment : the waters stood above the mountains. \q1
At thy rebuke they fled ; at the voice of thy thunder they hasted away. \q1
They go up by the mountains ; they go down by the valleys unto the place which thou hast founded for them.\f + \fr 104.8 \ft They go up…: or, The mountains ascend, the valleys descend\f* \q1
Thou hast set a bound that they may not pass over ; that they turn not again to cover the earth. \b \q1
He sendeth the springs into the valleys , \add which\add* run among the hills.\f + \fr 104.10 \ft He: Heb. Who\f*\f + \fr 104.10 \ft run: Heb. walk\f* \q1
They give drink to every beast of the field : the wild asses quench their thirst.\f + \fr 104.11 \ft quench: Heb. break\f* \q1
By them shall the fowls of the heaven have their habitation , \add which\add* sing among the branches.\f + \fr 104.12 \ft sing: Heb. give a voice\f* \q1
He watereth the hills from his chambers : the earth is satisfied with the fruit of thy works. \q1
He causeth the grass to grow for the cattle , and herb for the service of man : that he may bring forth food out of the earth ; \q1

And wine \add that\add* maketh glad the heart of man , \add and\add* oil to make \add his\add* face to shine , and bread \add which\add* strengtheneth man’s heart.\f + \fr 104.15 \ft oil…: Heb. to make his face shine with oil, or, more than oil\f* \q1
The trees of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* are full \add of sap;\add* the cedars of Lebanon , which he hath planted ; \q1
Where the birds make their nests : \add as for\add* the stork , the fir trees \add are\add* her house. \q1
The high hills \add are\add* a refuge for the wild goats ; \add and\add* the rocks for the conies. \b \q1
He appointed the moon for seasons : the sun knoweth his going down. \q1
Thou makest darkness , and it is night : wherein all the beasts of the forest do creep \add forth\add*.\f + \fr 104.20 \ft beasts…: Heb. beasts thereof do trample on the forest\f* \q1
The young lions roar after their prey , and seek their meat from God. \q1
The sun ariseth , they gather themselves together , and lay them down in their dens. \q1
Man goeth forth unto his work and to his labour until the evening. \q1
O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, how manifold are thy works ! in wisdom hast thou made them all: the earth is full of thy riches. \q1
\add So is\add* this great and wide sea , wherein \add are\add* things creeping innumerable , both small and great beasts. \q1
There go the ships : \add there is\add* that leviathan , \add whom\add* thou hast made to play therein.\f + \fr 104.26 \ft made: Heb. formed\f* \q1
These wait all upon thee; that thou mayest give \add them\add* their meat in due season. \q1
\add That\add* thou givest them they gather : thou openest thine hand , they are filled with good. \q1
Thou hidest thy face , they are troubled : thou takest away their breath , they die , and return to their dust. \q1
Thou sendest forth thy spirit , they are created : and thou renewest the face of the earth. \b \q1

The glory of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* shall endure for ever : the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* shall rejoice in his works.  +  r 104.31  t endure: Heb. be * \q1
He looketh on the earth , and it trembleth : he toucheth the hills , and they smoke. \q1
I will sing unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* as long as I live : I will sing praise to my God while I have my being. \q1
My meditation of him shall be sweet : I will be glad in the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*. \q1

Let the sinners be consumed out of the earth , and let the wicked be no more. Bless thou the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, O my soul. Praise ye the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*
d*.
